# Working without Xcode command-line tools

**Problem:** `cargo build`, `cargo test`, and `cargo clippy` need a working C toolchain for native crates (`ring`, `aws-lc-sys`, `libsqlite3-sys`, etc.). Without Xcode command-line tools, linking often fails.

**Context:** Workspace members transitively depend on native crates (e.g. `quant`, `nats_adapter`, `api`/`sqlx`, `ledger`). There is no fully “pure Rust” path for the whole workspace.

## What works without Xcode

| Tool | Use |
|------|-----|
| `rustfmt --edition 2021 --check` | Format check (no link) |
| `rg` / `grep` | Structure and pattern search |
| `cargo metadata` | Dependency graph analysis |
| Editor / `rust-analyzer` | Navigation (if installed) |

## What needs Xcode (or another working `cc`)

| Tool | Why |
|------|-----|
| `cargo build` / `cargo test` / `cargo clippy` / `cargo check` | Native crate link + build scripts |

## Workflow without Xcode

1. **Format:** `cd agents/backend && cargo fmt --check` (or `rustfmt` on changed files).
2. **Static review:** signatures, `From` impls, `#[derive]`, module wiring.
3. **Before full verification:** install CLI tools (`xcode-select --install` or switch Xcode path), then `cd agents/backend && cargo build && cargo test`.

**Parity:** Same guidance as `.opencode/rules/work-without-xcode.md` (OpenCode).
